Set up and start the webserver
================================

1. Install node.js on the machine, either using the online installer or
via package manager:
https://nodejs.org/en/download/package-manager/

2. run 'npm install' in your command line to install all dependencies specified
in package.json

3. start the webserver by typing 'npm start'

4. You can access the webserver by calling 'http://localhost:3000' in your browser
